                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>This daemonic disease turns the victim into a hadi.</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[type:fortitude|dc:19]</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> carrier (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 1} (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 2} (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 5</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 3} (1 week)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 6</strong> transform into a hadi (1 year). For a PC, the best way to model this is to replace ancestry Hit Points, size, Speeds, ability boosts, ability flaws, traits, and special abilities with those of the ratfolk ancestry. The character loses previous ancestry feats, selecting replacements from the ratfolk ancestry.</p>"
                },
